  "section_id": "41-optical-engines",
  "title": "Optical Engines",
  "title_translation": null,
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "id": "p000",
      "index": 0,
      "source": "Nvidia’s X800-Q3450 CPO switch features 115.2T total throughput and is designed for use with the scale-out network. The initial version will use 72 optical engines each operating at 1.6Tbit/s; later versions will likely transition to 36 optical engines at 3.2Tbit/s each, costing ~$1,000 per unit (including FAUs). As a result, the total BOM cost for the optical engines amounts to around $35-40k (for the 3.2T OE version).",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [],
      "parent_block_id": "b0568",
